<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-21T12:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-19T23:07:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4728: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-06-21T12:24:00-05:00" notBefore="1919-06-20T09:00:00+04:53"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 21, 1919, 12:24
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>From [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                        <p>“270, June 20, 9 a.m. <persName corresp="#p_GGGR1">General
                                Gaida</persName> returned suddenly and unexpectedly to Omsk
                            yesterday. I had interview with him. <persName corresp="#p_GGGR1">Gaida</persName> is despondent, has aged in appearance, and is
                            discouraged as to future of military situation. Informed me that in all
                            probability he would retire and eventually go to France. He said
                                <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> was surrounded by a
                            clique of Russian officers who were intriguing against him. <persName corresp="#p_GGGR1">Gaida</persName> believes Bolsheviki will not be
                            defeated by Siberian Army and that overthrow of Bolshevism is not yet in
                            sight. Bolsheviki are larger in number and now are [better?] equipped
                            with guns than Siberian forces. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>